  "texts": [
    "A common misconception is that the model directly stores data by compressing the training tokens.",
    "One can understand that this is not the case by calculating a token compression rate in tokens per learnable parameter.",
    "GPT-3 has 175/300 = 0.6 tokens per learnable parameter, which is hardly any compression at all.",
    "That is, if one interprets this metric as the model using one ANN parameter to carry the information in a little less than one token, then one cannot interpret the model to be simply a memory model.",
    "In other words, we know that the \"black box\" has many artificial neurons, but we do not understand how they operate collectively to implement a cognitive function of language understanding, language generation, and common-sense knowledge."
  ],
